SIMPLE: ex_parte
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ex parte
<hw>Ex` par"te</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L. See <er>Ex-</er>, and
<er>Part</er>.]</ety> <def>Upon or from one side only; one-sided;
partial; <as>as, an <ex>ex parte</ex> statement</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Ex parte application</b></col>, <cd>one made without
notice or opportunity to oppose.</cd> -- <col><b>Ex parte
council</b></col>, <cd>one that assembles at the request of only one of
the parties in dispute.</cd> -- <mcol><col><b>Ex parte hearing</b></col>
<it>or</it> <col><b>Ex parte evidence</b></col></mcol> <fld>(Law)</fld>,
<cd>that which is had or taken by one side or party in the absence of
the other. Hearings before grand juries, and affidavits, are <ex>ex
parte</ex>.</cd> <rj><au>Wharton's Law Dict.</au>
<au>Burrill.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Expatiate</ent>⟦br⟧
